{
  "texts": [
    "The Levenshtein Ratio (LRa) is a similarity measure derived from the LD according to the following expression, where LD(a, b) is the LD between two strings a and b, and A and B are the respective lengths of each of those strings.",
    "The LRa provides a value between 0 and 1, where 0 means the two strings are completely dissimilar, and 1 means they are identical.",
    "We first propose two metrics based on the concept of LRa: the Average Levenshtein Index of Dissimilarity (ALID) and the Levenshtein Recall (LR).",
    "These aim to capture the effectiveness of anonymization when there is no information about the nature of each token (i.e., whether it constitutes a sensitive entity or not) while tackling the limitations of string matching.",
    "The computations of both these metrics are formalized next."
  ]
}